LIMITATION OF LIABILITY FOR BUDGET ENFORCEMENT
===============================================

banto is a budget management aid, not a guarantee against excessive
API charges. The authors and copyright holders shall not be liable for
any direct, indirect, incidental, special, exemplary, or consequential
damages (including, but not limited to, unexpected API charges,
financial losses, or service interruptions) arising from:

  (a) Inaccuracies in the bundled or user-configured pricing table,
      including outdated or incorrect per-model rates;

  (b) Budget overruns caused by software defects, configuration
      errors, race conditions, or unforeseen usage patterns;

  (c) Agents or processes that bypass banto's API and access API keys
      or provider services through other means (e.g., direct Keychain
      queries, environment variables, or alternate credential stores);

  (d) Changes in provider pricing that are not reflected in the
      user's configuration;

  (e) Any other circumstances in which actual API charges exceed the
      budget limits configured in banto.

Users are solely responsible for monitoring their actual API spend
through each provider's billing dashboard and for configuring banto's
pricing table to reflect current provider rates.
